  "prompt": "Where can I find device art generators for Samsung S5?",
  "response": "Finding device art generators for the Samsung Galaxy S5 can be somewhat challenging, as these tools are more commonly available for the latest devices due to demand. However, here are a few approaches you might take:\n\n1. **Google's Device Art Generator**: Google has a device art generator that was part of the Android Developer Tools. While it may not have the Samsung Galaxy S5 as a default option, you can check for older versions or updates that might include it.\n\n2. **Photoshop or GIMP Templates**: You may find downloadable templates for Photoshop or GIMP that include the Samsung Galaxy S5. Websites like Dribbble, DeviantArt, or community forums for graphic designers may offer these templates for download.\n\n3. **Online Marketplaces**: Websites like Creative Market or GraphicRiver might sell device mockup templates that include the Galaxy S5. These usually come in PSD format and can be edited with software like Adobe Photoshop.\n\n4. **Custom Mockups**: If readily available solutions are not sufficient, consider creating your own mockups using Photoshop or another graphic design tool. You can use images of the Samsung Galaxy S5 and overlay your screenshots onto them.\n\n5. **Community Forums and GitHub**: Sometimes developers share their own tools or scripts on forums or platforms like GitHub. A search may uncover a project that includes an S5 device frame.\n\n6. **Freelancers**: If the above options are not fruitful, you could hire a freelancer to create a custom device art generator for you via platforms like Upwork or Fiverr.\n\nEnsure that any resources you download or purchase are legitimate and safe to use to avoid security risks.",
